title: The Footy Show (AFL) - What a big 12 years
description:
"What a big week in football!" For twelve remarkable years, it was the line that Eddie McGuire used so many times to open another episode of the television phenomenon that is "The Footy Show".

From humble and uncertain beginnings, Eddie along with the ever controversial Sam Newman and "Our best mate
behind the bar", comedian Trevor Marmalade, turned a crazy, impulsive concept into "must see" TV for all footy fans
and a ratings winner for The Nine Network.

Hosted by Sam & Trevor, "What A Big 12 Years in Football" stands as a fitting farewell to Eddie McGuire as he moves from unflappable (most of the time) TV host to the next challenge in his astonishing career as CEO of The Nine Network.
